  16,35,"And the idolaters (those who associated others with Allah) said, \"Had Allah pleased we had not served aught beside Him, neither we nor our fathers; nor had we forbidden aught without His permission\". Even so did those before them. Are the messen"
  16,36,"Verily, We have sent to every nation a Messenger, proclaiming, \"Serve you Allah, and avoid Taghut (false gods).\" And amongst them are some whom Allah has guided, and amongst them are some for whom error has become established. So travel through"
  16,37,"If you are eager for their guidance, verily, Allah guides not those who go astray (or mislead), nor have they any helpers"
  16,38,"They swear by their strongest oath, \"Allah will not raise up him who dies.\"- Nay! But it is a promise binding on Him in truth. But most know not"
  16,39,"(It is) To explain to them that which they disputed about, and that those who disbelieved may know that they are liars"
  16,40,"We only say unto a thing We intend, the Word, \"BE,\" and it is"
  16,41,"But those who fled their homes for AllahÂ´s sake, after they were wronged (oppressed), We will surely establish them in this world with good things; but truly the reward of the Hereafter is greater, if you did but know"
  16,42,"Those who are patient, and put their trust (or reliance) upon their Lord"